		<main class="picturesInfo">
			<article>
				<img
					src="/diabetes-awareness-and-action/media/management/coach.jpg"
					alt="Nutrition coach holding a clipboard and smiling."
				/>
				<div class="info">
					<li>
						If you are overweight or have obesity, work with your
						health care team to create a weight-loss plan.
					</li>
					<li>
						The Body Weight Planner can help you tailor your calorie
						and physical activity plans to reach & maintain your
						goal weight.
					</li>
					<li>
						For more information, visit <a
							href="https://www.niddk.nih.gov/bwp"
							target="_blank"
							><span class="bold1"
								>https://www.niddk.nih.gov/bwp</span
							></a
						>.
					</li>
				</div>
			</article>
			<article>
				<img
					src="/diabetes-awareness-and-action/media/management/yoga.jpg"
					alt="Pregnant woman doing a butterfly stretch."
				/>
				<div class="info">
					<li>
						To lose weight, you need to eat fewer calories and
						replace less healthy foods with foods lower in calories,
						fat, and sugar.
					</li>
					<li>
						If you have diabetes, are overweight or obese, and are
						planning to have a baby, you should try to lose any
						excess weight before you become pregnant.
					</li>
					<li>
						Learn more about planning for pregnancy if you have
						diabetes.
					</li>
